@endnode

@node hidden
@title "Hidden Files"
Hidden Files:
If not selected, Visual doesn't display file or directory that have
the protect bit 'H'
(The '.ICN' file must have the protect bit 'H' too otherwise
 the file will be display)
@endnode

@node parent
@title "Parent Thumbnail"
Parent Thumbnail: 
If selected, show a thumbnail for the parent directory 
(if you modify it, rescan the directory to see changes)
@endnode

@node icndir
@title "Icn Dir"
Icn Dir. :
directory where Visual searchs for the defaults thumbnails
(def_file,def_dir,def_volume,def_assign)
@endnode

@node palette
@title "Palette"
@{u}Palette:@{uu}
the name of the palette file to be used
@endnode

@node command
@title "The Preferences"
@{u}Command:@{uu}
the filename of the command that will be launched if a file is
double-clicked
ex: DTActions %s
(%s must be present and will be replaced by the name of the file)

You can use MegaView or whatever program you want.

MegaView was written by Hans-Jörg Frieden in 1993
@endnode

@node arexxdir
@title "ARexx Dir"
@{u}ARexx Dir.:@{uu}
The directory where the ARexx script are
@endnode

@node arexxscript
@title "ARexx Script"
@{u}ARexx script:@{uu}
the name of the script to be used to generate thumbnails
@endnode

@node size
@title "Box Width, Box Height, Thumbnail Width, Thumbnail Height"
@{u}Box Width, Box Height:@{uu}
width of the box which is diplay around the thumbnails

@{u}Thumbnail Width, Thumbnail Height:@{uu}
width and height of the thumbnails
These numbers are only useful for an ARexx script
@endnode

@node autolayout
@title "Auto Layout"
@endnode

@node arexx
@title "ARexx Interface"

To generate '.ICN' file, you can do it yourself with any graphic program
or with the arexx script.
In an ARexx script, you will have to use commands to control Visual and
your graphic program.
You will need to send command to Visual to get the name of the file
and to get the preference width , height and palette filename.

Some script are provided in this archive (for ImageFX2.0 ImageFX1.5
ImageFX1.03 and ADPro , the script for ImageFX2.0 are the script I use)

Visual accepts 6 commands.

CHECK

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Check

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return information about the CANCEL gadget.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a result of 0 if the CANCEL gadget has not been pressed
      otherwise a result of 5
     
GETMAIN

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      GetMain

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return information.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a string containing information, in the following format:

         "filename_of_the_palette" width height

GETSELECTED

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      GetSelected

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Return the name of the first FILE selected and if this file
      isn't on the Visual window, put it on the window.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      Returns a string containing the filename.


MESSAGE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Message Text

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Display a message in the window of Visual.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      @{u}Text@{uu}
         Text of the message.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

UNSELECT

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      UnSelect

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Unselect the first file selected.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

UPDATE

   @{b}FORMAT@{ub}
      Update

   @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
      Unselect the first file selected and reload its icone.

   @{b}INPUTS@{ub}
      None.

   @{b}RESULT@{ub}
      None.

@endnode

